sentences: Louise Elizabeth Redknapp (née Nurding, born 4 November 1974), is an English singer, songwriter and media personality.
She was a member of Eternal, a R&B girl group which debuted in 1993 with their quadruple-platinum studio album Always & Forever.
In 1995, she departed from the group for a solo career, in which she released the platinum-selling albums Naked (1996), Woman in Me (1997) and Elbow Beach (2000).

At the age of 11, she won a scholarship to the Italia Conti Academy of Theatre Arts in London, where she met her future Eternal colleague Kéllé Bryan on her first day.
Kéllé and Louise, together with sisters Easther and Vernie Bennett, formed the band Eternal in 1992.
The group performed R&B, and recorded a number of hits during the 1990s.

Louise left the group in 1995 to pursue a solo career, amid unsubstantiated rumours that she was forced to leave because a radio station in the United States dedicated to black music would not promote the racially mixed group.
In late 1995, Louise signed a record deal with First Avenue management and EMI Records.
